HEADWORD: madeira winter cherry
<hw>madeira winter cherry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
small South American shrub (<spn>Solanum pseudocapsicum</spn>)
cultivated as a houseplant for its abundant ornamental but poisonous red
or yellow cherrylike fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Jerusalem cherry, winter cherry, Madeira winter
cherry, <spn>Solanum pseudocapsicum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madeira wood</ent>⟦br⟧
